SIMPLE: thirsty
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thirsty
<hw>Thirst"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Thirstier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>superl.</pos> <adjf>Thirstiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[AS.
<ets><?/urstig</ets>. See <er>Thirst</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Feeling thirst; having a painful or distressing
sensation from want of drink; hence, having an eager desire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Give me, I pray thee, a little water to drink, for I am
<qex>thirsty</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Judges iv. 19.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Deficient in moisture; dry; parched.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A dry and <qex>thirsty</qex> land, where no water is.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. lxiii. 1.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When in the sultry glebe I faint,⟦br⟧
Or on the <qex>thirsty</qex> mountain pant.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thirteen</ent>⟦br⟧
